            <group xml:id="fr_Prolusioni"> <!--TESTO FRANCESE DELLE 3 PROLUSIONI-->
                <text xml:id="fr_Prolusione-1"> <!--FR 1 PROLUSIONE-->
                    <body xml:lang="fr" source="#Bouquet-Engler2002" xml:id="body-francese">
                        <!--Sedicesima pagina-->
                        <pb n="f1r" xml:id="body_p18" facs="#scan_p18"/>
                        <!--Numeri impaginazione a stampa e a mano-->
                        <ab>
                            <fw type="pageNum" xml:id="HandPageNumber-18" rend="align(left)" facs="#facs_HandPageNumber-18"> 18 </fw>
                        </ab>
                        <div xml:id="div_p18_fr" hand="#h1" type="box_testo" >
                            <ab xml:id="pericope_91Aaaa056" n="56" xml:lang="FR" corresp="#it_91Aaaa056 #en_91Aaaa056" facs="#facs_pericope_91Aaaa056" part="F" >
                                <lb xml:id="lb1_p18" n="1" facs="#facs_p18_lb1"/> 
                                il ne suit pas que la <choice cert="high"><abbr>geolog<am>.</am></abbr><expan>géolog<ex>ie</ex></expan></choice> soit une <term ref="#science_historique" rend="underline">science</term>
                                <lb xml:id="lb2_p18" n="2" facs="#facs_p18_lb2"/> 
                                <term ref="#science_historique">historique</term>, au moins au sens étroit et précis
                                <lb xml:id="lb3_p18" n="3" facs="#facs_p18_lb3"/>
                                que nous donnons à ce <term ref="#terme1">terme</term>.                            
                            </ab>                           
                            <ab xml:id="pericope_91Aaaa057" n="57" xml:lang="FR" corresp="#it_91Aaaa057 #en_91Aaaa057" facs="#facs_pericope_91Aaaa057"> 
                                <lb xml:id="lb4_p18" n="4" facs="#facs_p18_lb4"/> 
                                <choice cert="medium"><abbr>2a</abbr><expan>seconde</expan></choice> condition<unclear reason="illegible"><del rend="overstrike"></del></unclear> impliquée par le <term ref="#mot">mot</term> de <term ref="#science_historique">science</term>
                                <lb xml:id="lb5_p18" n="5" facs="#facs_p18_lb5"/>
                                <choice cert="high"><abbr >historiq<am>.</am></abbr><expan>historiq<ex>ue</ex></expan></choice><supplied reason="omitted-in-original" ><pc type="interrogative">?</pc></supplied> <pc type="dash">-</pc> C'est que l'<term ref="#objet">objet</term> qui fait la <term ref="#matière">matière</term> de 
                                <lb xml:id="lb6_p18" n="6" facs="#facs_p18_lb6"/>
                                l'<term ref="#histoire">histoire</term><add place="margin" xml:id="aggiunta4" facs="#add4" resp="#ADS"> - <choice><abbr>p. ex.</abbr><expan xml:id="expan6" facs="#abbrev6">par exemple</expan></choice> l'art, la religion, le costume, etc. - </add>représente, dans un <term ref="#glossa-mancante">sens</term> quelconque, des                                
                                <lb xml:id="lb7_p18" n="7" facs="#facs_p18_lb7"/>
                                <term ref="#acte_humain" rend ="underline">actes humains</term>, régis par la <term ref="#volonté">volonté</term> et l'<term ref="#intelligence">intelligence</term>
                                <lb xml:id="lb8_p18" n="8" facs="#facs_p18_lb8"/>
                                humaines, <pc type="dash">-</pc> et qui d'ailleurs doivent être tels
                                <lb xml:id="lb9_p18" n="9" facs="#facs_p18_lb9"/>
                                qu'ils <add place="overline" >n'</add>intéressent pas seulement l'<term ref="#glossa-mancante">individu</term> mais <del rend="overstrike" cert="medium">une</del>
                                <lb xml:id="lb10_p18" n="10" facs="#facs_p18_lb10"/>
                                la <term ref="#glossa-mancante">collectivité</term>.<unclear reason="illegible"><del rend="overstrike"><gap/></del></unclear>                                                                
                            </ab>
                            <ab xml:id="pericope_91Aaaa058" n="58" xml:lang="FR" corresp="#it_91Aaaa058 #en_91Aaaa058" facs="#facs_pericope_91Aaaa058">
                                <lb xml:id="lb11_p18" n="11" facs="#facs_p18_lb11"/>
                                Les faits linguistiques peuvent-ils passer
                                <lb xml:id="lb12_p18" n="12" facs="#facs_p18_lb12"/>
                                pour être le résultat d'actes <del rend="overstrike" ></del>
                                <lb xml:id="lb13_p18" n="13" facs="#facs_p18_lb13"/> 
                                de notre volonté<pc type="interrogative">?</pc> Telle est donc la question. La 
                                <lb xml:id="lb14_p18" n="14" facs="#facs_p18_lb14"/> 
                                <term ref="#science_du_langage">science du langage</term>, actuelle, yrépond affirmativement.                                
                            </ab>
                            <ab xml:id="pericope_91Aaaa059" n="59" xml:lang="FR" corresp="#it_91Aaaa059 #en_91Aaaa059" facs="#facs_pericope_91Aaaa059">
                                <lb xml:id="lb15_p18" n="15" facs="#facs_p18_lb15"/>
                                Seulement il faut ajouter aussitôt 
                                <add place="margin">qu'il y a beaucoup de <term ref="#glossa-mancante">degrés</term> connus, comme nous savons, dans la <term ref="#volonté">volonté</term> <term ref="#conscience">consciente</term> ou <term ref="#inconscience">inconsciente<supplied reason="omitted-in-original"><pc type="semicolon">;</pc></supplied></term></add>
                                <subst><del rend="overstrike"></del><add> or</add></subst><supplied reason="omitted-in-original">,</supplied> de tous 
                                <lb xml:id="lb16_p18" n="16" facs="#facs_p18_lb16"/>
                                les actes qu'on pourrait mettre en parallèle, 
                                <lb xml:id="lb17_p18" n="17" facs="#facs_p18_lb17"/> 
                                l'<term ref="#acte_linguistique">acte linguistique</term>, si je puis le nommer ainsi, <subst><del></del><add place="above">a ce caractère d'être</add></subst>  
                                <lb xml:id="lb18_p18" n="18" facs="#facs_p18_lb18"/> 
                                le moins <term ref="#reflechi">réfléchi</term>, le moins prémédité, <unclear reason ="illegible" cert="medium"><del rend="overstrike" cert="medium">le</del></unclear>
                                <lb xml:id="lb19_p18" n="19" facs="#facs_p18_lb19"/>
                                <unclear><del>plus machinal, en mir temps que le</del></unclear>en même
                                <lb xml:id="lb20_p18" n="20" facs="#facs_p18_lb20"/>
                                temps que le plus impersonnel de tous.
                            </ab> 
                            <ab xml:id="pericope_91Aaaa060" n="60" xml:lang="FR" corresp="#it_91Aaaa060 #en_91Aaaa060" facs="#facs_pericope_91Aaaa060">
                                Il y a 
                                <lb xml:id="lb21_p18" n="21" facs="#facs_p18_lb21"/>
                                là une <term ref="#différence1">différence de degré</term>, qui va si loin qu'elle
                                <lb xml:id="lb22_p18" n="22" facs="#facs_p18_lb22"/> 
                                a longtemps donné l'illusion d'<choice cert="high"><abbr>1</abbr><expan>une</expan></choice> <term ref="#différence1">différence es<pc force="weak">-</pc></term>
                                <lb xml:id="lb23_p18" n="23" facs="#facs_p18_lb23"/>
                                <pc>-</pc><term ref="#différence1">sentielle</term>, mais qui n'est en réalité qu'<choice cert="high"><abbr>1</abbr><expan>une</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>diff<am>.</am></abbr><expan>diff<ex>érence</ex></expan></choice> de degrés.                                                            
                            </ab>
                        </div>
                    </body> 
                </text>
            </group>  
            
            <group xml:id="it_Prolusioni" xml:lang="IT"> <!--TRADUZIONI ITALIANO DELLE 3 PROLUSIONI-->
                <text xml:id="it_Prolusione-1"> <!--ITA 1 PROLUSIONE-->
                    <body source="#Fadda2006" resp="#EF" xml:id="body-italiano">
                        <div xml:id="div_p18_it" hand="#h1" type="box_testo_it">
                            <ab xml:id="it_91Aaaa056" corresp="#pericope_91Aaaa056" xml:lang="IT" part="F">
                                <lb/>che non segue però che la geologia 
                                <lb/>sia una scienza storica, per lo meno nel senso stretto e preciso  
                                <lb/>che noi conferiamo a questo termine.                      
                            </ab>
                            <ab xml:id="it_91Aaaa057" corresp="#pericope_91Aaaa057" xml:lang="IT" part="F">
                                <lb/>Qual è dunque la seconda condizione implicata dall’espressione ‘scienza  
                                <lb/>storica’? - Si tratta del fatto che l’oggetto che fa la materia  
                                <lb/>della storia – per esempio l’arte, la religione, l’abbigliamento, ecc. – rappresenta, in un senso qualsiasi,  
                                <lb/>degli atti umani, governati dalla volontà e dall’intelligenza  
                                <lb/>umane – e che d’altronde devono essere tali  
                                <lb/>da non interessare solo l’individuo,  
                                <lb/>ma la collettività.
                            </ab>
                            <ab xml:id="it_91Aaaa058" corresp="#pericope_91Aaaa058" xml:lang="IT">
                                I fatti linguistici possono passare per essere il risultato di atti  
                                <lb/>della nostra volontà? Questa è dunque la questione. La  
                                <lb/>scienza del linguaggio attuale vi risponde affermativamente.                          
                            </ab>       
                            <ab xml:id="it_91Aaaa059" corresp="#pericope_91Aaaa059" xml:lang="IT">
                                <lb/>Soltanto, bisogna aggiungere anche che ci sono molti gradi conosciuti, come sappiamo, nella volontà cosciente e incosciente; ora, di tutti
                                <lb/>gli atti che si potrebbero mettere in parallelo,  
                                <lb/>l’atto linguistico, se posso chiamarlo così, ha questo carattere d’essere  
                                <lb/>il meno riflessivo, il meno premeditato,  
                                <lb/>e al contempo il più impersonale di tutti.
                            </ab>                               
                            <ab xml:id="it_91Aaaa060" corresp="#pericope_91Aaaa060" xml:lang="IT">
                                C’è  
                                <lb/>una differenza di grado, così spinta  
                                <lb/>da aver dato l’illusione d’una differenza  
                                <lb/>essenziale, ma che in realtà è solo una differenza di gradi.
                            </ab>                                                                                               
                        </div>                            
                    </body>
                </text>          
            </group>

            <group xml:id="en_Prolusioni" xml:lang="EN" > <!--TRADUZIONI INGLESE DELLE 3 PROLUSIONI-->
                <text xml:id="en_Prolusione-1"> <!--EN 1 PROLUSIONE-->
                    <body resp="#AC" xml:id="body-inglese" source="#WGL">
                        <div xml:id="div_p18_en" hand="#h1" type="box_testo_en">
                            <ab xml:id="en_91Aaaa056" corresp="#pericope_91Aaaa056" xml:lang="EN">
                                <lb/>from this it does not follow that geology 
                                <lb/>is a historical science, at least not in the narrow, precise sense 
                                <lb/>we are giving this term.
                            </ab>
                            <ab xml:id="en_91Aaaa057" corresp="#pericope_91Aaaa057" xml:lang="EN">
                                <lb/>What then is the second condition that the term historical science 
                                <lb/>implies? It is that the object which makes up the stuff of history
                                <lb/>- for example art, religion, costume, etc. - stands in any of its senses, 
                                <lb/>for human actions, dependent on human intelligence and will -
                                <lb/>and, moreover, necessarily 
                                <lb/>interests not only the individual
                                <lb/>but the community.
                            </ab>        
                            <ab xml:id="en_91Aaaa058" corresp="#pericope_91Aaaa058" xml:lang="EN">
                                Can linguistic facts be said to be the result 
                                <lb/>of acts of will? That is the question. The 
                                <lb/>current science of language gives a positive answer.                        
                            </ab>    
                            <ab xml:id="en_91Aaaa059" corresp="#pericope_91Aaaa059" xml:lang="EN">                                
                                <lb/>However, one should add immediately that there are many degrees of conscious or unconscious will; furthermore, of all 
                                <lb/>the acts which can be compared, 
                                <lb/>the linguistic act, if I might call it that, is characterized as being 
                                <lb/>the least reflected on, the least premeditated, 
                                <lb/>as well as the most impersonal of all.
                            </ab>
                            <ab xml:id="en_91Aaaa060" corresp="#pericope_91Aaaa060" xml:lang="EN">
                                That 
                                <lb/>constitutes a difference of degree, which is so far-reaching 
                                <lb/>as to have long appeared a fundamental difference 
                                <lb/>of degree, even though it is but a difference of degree.
                            </ab>
                        </div>   
                    </body>
                </text>       
            </group>
